<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Coppola Goes Back to Roots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROME (AP) -- Francis Ford Coppola is getting back to his roots,  
camera in hand. 
</P>
<P>
	Coppola's grandfather, Agostino, emigrated to United States from  
Bernalda in the southern province of Basilicata and the director 
still has relatives there. 
</P>
<P>
	In an interview with the daily Corriere della Sera published  
Sunday, the director said he has been filming Bernalda's streets 
and houses, his relatives and the festival honoring the town's 
patron saint. 
</P>
<P>
	In ``Godfather III,'' Coppola recreated the colorful festival,  
which he said his father Carmine had told him about ``a hundred 
times.'' Coppola also cast a cousin from Bernalda in a small role. 
</P>
<P>
	Returning to his roots puts him back in touch with the ``real  
value of things,'' Coppola said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
