<HEADLINE> Tout Charmant Wins Del Mar Oaks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Tout Charmant rallied in the stretch and  
beat Smooth Player by a length to win the $250,000 Del Mar Oaks on 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by David Flores and carrying 121 pounds, Tout Charmant  
covered 1 1/8 miles on the turf in 1:48 3-5 to prevail in a field of 
10 3-year-old fillies. 
</P>
<P>
	Tout Charmant earned $150,000 for Walter Family Trust and paid  
$21.60, $10.60 and $6.20. Smooth Player returned $13.60 and $7.20, 
while Sweet Ludy, another 1 3/4 lengths back in third, paid $4.40 to 
show. 
  	   	
</P>
