<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Orioles Lose Two Pitchers to Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- The Baltimore Orioles had two pitchers leave  
the game with injuries Sunday during their game against the Chicago 
White Sox. 
</P>
<P>
	Starter Mike Mussina left in the third inning after being hit in  
the right shoulder by a line drive off the bat of Brook Fordyce. He 
tried to throw, but experienced discomfort and could not continue. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury was diagnosed as a bruise and X-rays were negative.  
</P>
<P>
	Mussina threw 32 pitches, 22 of them strikes. He will  
re-evalutated before his next scheduled start. 
</P>
<P>
	Mussina's replacement, left-hander Arthur Rhodes, left the game  
in the fourth inning after tumbling from the mound in an effort to 
field a grounder by Chris Singleton. He hurt the index finger of 
his left hand and, like Mussina, left after taking a few practice 
throws from the mound. 
</P>
<P>
	Doug Johns replaced Rhodes.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
