<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> S.African Breaks Breaststroke Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- Penny Heyns of South Africa broke the  
world record for the women's 100-meter breaststroke at the Pan 
Pacific swimming championships on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Heyns' time of 1 minute, 6.52 seconds in a qualifying heat broke  
her own record of 1:06.95, which she set in Los Angeles on July 19. 
</P>
<P>
	It was her fifth world record in a month and she will have two  
more chances to lower it in the semifinals on Monday and Tuesday's 
final. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
