<HEADLINE> Boy Dies on Ride at Calif. Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) -- A 12-year-old boy was killed after  
falling from a ride at Paramount's Great America Theme Park. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy, whose name has not been released, fell from his seat on  
the Drop Zone Stunt Tower about 3:20 p.m. Sunday, park spokesman 
Timothy Chanaud said. 
</P>
<P>
	The ride, which opened in 1996, free-falls 129 feet at 62 mph.  
No one had been killed or seriously hurt on the ride before Sunday, 
he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Part of the park was immediately shut down and will remain  
closed through Monday. 
  	   	
