<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Galaxy 4, MetroStars 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PASADENA, Calif. (AP) -- Carlos Hermosillo and Zak Ibsen each  
scored twice as the Los Angeles Galaxy defeated the New York-New 
Jersey MetroStars 4-1 Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The Galaxy's fourth consecutive win put Los Angeles (15-8)  
within three points of first-place Colorado in the Major League 
Soccer's Western Conference. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars (5-19) lost their ninth in a row, tying a league  
record. 
</P>
<P>
	Hermosillo scored the game's first goal in the eighth minute  
when he headed Greg Vanney's corner kick to the right of goalkeeper 
Mike Ammann. 
</P>
<P>
	Nine minutes later, Ibsen extended the margin by scoring inside  
the left post from eight yards. 
</P>
<P>
	Hermosillo's second goal gave the Galaxy a 3-0 lead in the 59th  
minute. Ammann tipped Jones' crossing pass from the right side of 
the penalty area, but Hermosillo converted the deflecton into an 
empty net from six yards. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars' Mark Chung scored on a penalty kick in the 72nd  
minute. Then Ibsen scored inside the left post from seven yards. 
Vanney finished with three assists. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
