<HEADLINE> Lindo Plays Justice Clarence Thomas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- In a new biographical film, Delroy Lindo bent  
over backward to give Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas the 
benefit of the doubt. He's not sure audiences will do the same. 
</P>
<P>
	In the upcoming cable movie, ``Strange Justice,'' Lindo said  
fairness was his supreme goal. 
</P>
<P>
	The film deals with Thomas' Senate confirmation hearings in  
1991, which became controversial when former Thomas employee Anita 
Hill accused the judge of sexual harassment. Thomas was eventually 
confirmed by a narrow margin. 
</P>
<P>
	``I tried to play devil's advocate for Judge Thomas,'' Lindo  
says in Sunday's Daily News. ``I attempted to put myself in his 
place and develop a rationale for what he said and did. Despite my 
best efforts, I think the film comes out in favor of Anita Hill.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Lindo, 46, has feature film credits including ``Get Shorty,''  
``Ransom'' and ``A Life Less Ordinary.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
