<HEADLINE> Jamaican Carmaker Rolls Out First </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KINGSTON, Jamaica (AP) -- A fledgling Jamaican carmaker has  
rolled out its first model -- a light sports utility vehicle named 
the Island Cruzer. 
</P>
<P>
	The carmaker, Excel Motors, unveiled the first production model  
Friday at its plant in western Savanna-la-Mar. The company will 
build five Island Cruzers a week and sell them for $9,500 each, 
Excel Owner Patrick Marzouca said. 
</P>
<P>
	Marzouca said he is trying to market the car to local car rental  
agencies. 
</P>
<P>
	The vehicle sports a 1.5-liter Japanese engine. The chassis was  
developed by a Canadian company, but the rest of the car was 
designed by Jamaicans, Marzouca said. 
</P>
