<HEADLINE> Orioles Lose Two Pitchers to Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- The Baltimore Orioles had two pitchers leave  
the game with injuries Sunday during their game against the Chicago 
White Sox. 
</P>
<P>
	Starter Mike Mussina left in the third inning after being hit in  
the right shoulder by a line drive off the bat of Brook Fordyce. He 
tried to throw, but experienced discomfort and could not continue. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury was diagnosed as a bruise and X-rays were negative.  
</P>
