<HEADLINE> Burn 4, Fire 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- The Dallas Burn scored on all four shots in a  
shootout and edged the Chicago Fire 4-3 on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Fire forward Josh Wolff's second goal of the game with 39  
seconds to go tied it at 3. Chicago (12-11) was successful on only 
three of five shootout attempts. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas (13-12) went up 2-0 on goals by Ariel Graziani and Chad  
Deering late in the first half. A pass from Graziani sprung Deering 
at midfield and he beat Chicago goalkeeper Zach Thornton on a 
left-footer from the top of the 18-yard box. 
</P>
<P>
	Chicago countered quickly with Wolff's first goal and a header  
by Kema Kovalenko past Dallas keeper Matt Jordan. A goal by the 
Burn's Richard Farrer in the 56th minute appeared to put Dallas 
ahead to stay before Wolff's last-minute goal. 
</P>
<P>
	With the victory, Dallas moved into sole possession of third  
place in the Western Conference. 
  	   	
</P>
