<HEADLINE> Rodman Arrested on Drunk Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEWPORT BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Dennis Rodman was released from  
jail Sunday, several hours after police were called to a 
restaurant-bar by someone who said the flamboyant former NBA star 
was drunk and causing a disturbance. 
</P>
<P>
	The 38-year-old Rodman, known for dyeing his hair and numerous  
tattoos and body piercings, spent a few hours in custody before 
being released on his own recognizance, Sgt. Jim Kaminsky said. 
</P>
<P>
	Calls to Rodman's agent, Steve Chasman, seeking comment were not  
immediately returned. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman was booked for investigation of being intoxicated in a  
public place, a misdemeanor, Kaminsky said. Rodman was ordered to 
appear in court Oct. 1. Before then, prosecutors will determine 
whether to file any charges, Kaminsky said. 
</P>
<P>
	Police had few details of the incident, but the restaurant owner  
said it didn't appear to be instigated by Rodman. 
</P>
<P>
	``From what I understand, a woman was verbally abusing him, and  
he said something back to her, and her boyfriend grabbed him and 
the police were called,'' said Ralph Furra, whose wife Julie was 
managing the restaurant at the time. 
</P>
<P>
	Police arrested Rodman outside the restaurant, where he is a  
regular, Furra said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've never had any problems with him; he's well-behaved,''  
Furra said. 
</P>
<P>
	The police were called to the restaurant most likely by a  
customer or a bartender, Furra said. His wife did not place the 
call, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Another man arrested with Rodman, Donn Emerson, 36, was booked  
for investigation of obstructing a police officer. The details of 
his involvement and his relationship with Rodman weren't 
immediately known, Kaminsky said. 
</P>
<P>
	Emerson also was released on his own recognizance.  
</P>
<P>
	Rodman played for the Detroit Pistons, San Antonio Spurs and  
Chicago Bulls before joining the Los Angeles Lakers for a short 
stint this year. The Lakers waived him in April. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodman, who has made headlines off and on the court for years,  
has been sued twice this year. A Kentucky woman has filed suit 
against him in June, claiming he assaulted her in the lobby of a 
Las Vegas resort. 
</P>
<P>
	On May 19, a casino security guard sued Rodman, accusing him of  
grabbing her breast while she was working at the Las Vegas Hilton. 
</P>
<P>
	Three lawsuits filed in Las Vegas in June 1998 involve other  
allegations about Rodman's behavior in casinos. 
</P>
<P>
	A Las Vegas Hilton employee accused him of grabbing her and  
lifting her off the ground in April 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	A Las Vegas woman accused Rodman of sexually assaulting her in  
April 1998 at the Las Vegas Hilton. 
</P>
<P>
	A craps dealer at The Mirage filed a lawsuit alleging Rodman  
humiliated him at work by rubbing his groin and head. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
