<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Reaches 50 Homers Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Mark McGwire hit two home runs against the New  
York Mets on Sunday to become the first player to reach 50 homers 
in a season four straight years. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire's 50th came on a 1-0 count leading off the seventh  
inning against Jeff Tam. The ball just cleared the outstretched 
glove of Shawon Dunston in left-center and landed just past the 
396-foot sign. 
</P>
<P>
	That was a routine fly compared to his first shot.  
</P>
<P>
	Big Mac left his mark on Shea Stadium in the first inning. He  
hit a 1-1 pitch from Octavio Dotel 502 feet -- his longest of the 
season -- and left a dent about 60 feet high on the scoreboard in 
right-center. 
</P>
<P>
	The shot shattered a lightbulb in the 16 for Ray Lankford's  
number -- just a few feet below McGwire's 25. In the bottom of the 
third inning, a worker climbed up the back of the scoreboard to 
screw in a new bulb. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire moved ahead of his pace from his record 70-homer season,  
hitting No. 50 in the Cardinals' 124th game -- one game earlier than 
last year. That is the second fastest pace ever, behind only 
Chicago's Sammy Sosa -- who hit his 51st Saturday in the Cubs' 121st 
game. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire also tied Babe Ruth for the most 50-homer seasons in a  
career with four. Six players, including Sosa, have hit 50 in two 
seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire, who has 230 homers over the last four years, has seven  
multihomer games this year and 60 in his career. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
